commit.message: fixed cntrl-z + simple detect functionality; added MRCNN button
fixed MRCNN, works with window to backend, and fixed pushing to server. now just need to make an M button for using MRCNN and deploy
made major changes to OSM interface
fixed map display, should be rendering again
got a basic version of showing accountability
updated JS to use delete button
rectanglify works beautifully, now I need to make delete mask work
got rectanglify to work and push to frontend. it seems to miss some rectangles, and I need to make sure I can only click at full zoom. rectangles at the moment are okay, but deleting is necessary
wrote a function called merge_small that efffectively combines masks that overlap
mrccn detector class updated to split images of theoretically any size or do a single appropriately sized image
working on adding some functionality to Mask_RCNN_Detect.py
integrated basic version of mask cnn

working mask_rcnn locally (no GPU). Can integrate pretty easily. Training script in mrcnn, and demo_detect.ipynb has a demo of using mask_rcnn. Big thanks to matterport for implementing Mask_RCNN and helping people use it. the folder mrcnn comes from them and is needed for config.
